                                      muKern v.0.1.062026

A minimal microkernel design for x86_64, ARMv8-A and RV64, 
plus a working proof-of-concept that boots on all three
and drops you into a tiny shell.

You can find DESIGN and ROADMAP in docs/

BUILD & RUN

Toolchain setup (rootless container) is in INSTALL. Then:

    $ make all              # build all three kernels
    $ make run-x86_64       # boot in QEMU
    $ make run-arm64
    $ make run-riscv64

Quit QEMU with Ctrl-A then x.
